"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The code is incorrect because it uses a custom distance metric (get_point_distance) with DBSCAN, but the DBSCAN implementation in scikit-learn does not support custom distance metrics. The metric parameter in DBSCAN should be one of the options allowed by sklearn.metrics.pairwise_distances for its metric parameter.\", \"patch\": \"28c28\\n< clustering = DBSCAN(metric=get_point_distance).fit(np.array([[point] for point in points]))\\n---\\n> clustering = DBSCAN(metric='euclidean').fit(np.array([point.to_list() for point in points]))\"}"